SIMPLE: carnosity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carnosity
<hw>Car*nos"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>carnosit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A fleshy excrescence; esp. a small
excrescence or fungous growth.</def> <rj><au>Wiseman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fleshy substance or quality; fleshy
covering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Consciences] overgrown with so hard a <qex>carnosity</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spelman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The olives, indeed be very small there, and bigger than capers;
yet commended they are for their <qex>carnosity</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carnot's cycle</ent>⟦br⟧
